stateDiagram-v2
    %% Figure 5.4b — PWA Offline-First Cache and Sync Logic

    [*] --> Online: App loads

    state Online {
        [*] --> Fresh: Service Worker installed
        Fresh --> Cached: Serwist caches static assets + API responses
        Cached --> Serving: Serve from cache-first strategy
        Serving --> Updated: New SW version detected
        Updated --> Serving: skipWaiting + clients.claim
    }

    Online --> Offline: Network lost (navigator.onLine = false)

    state Offline {
        [*] --> CacheHit: Request matches cached response
        CacheHit --> ServeStale: Return stale data from SW cache
        ServeStale --> QueueMutation: User performs write action
        QueueMutation --> PendingQueue: Store in IndexedDB queue
        PendingQueue --> WaitReconnect: Wait for connectivity
    }

    Offline --> Reconnecting: Network restored

    state Reconnecting {
        [*] --> DrainQueue: Replay queued mutations (FIFO)
        DrainQueue --> Revalidate: Re-fetch stale cached data
        Revalidate --> Synced: All data consistent
    }

    Reconnecting --> Online: Sync complete

    note right of Offline
        🔴 Offline Banner shown in UI
        "You are currently offline.
         Changes will sync when
         connection is restored."
    end note

    note right of Online
        🟢 Full functionality
        Real-time notifications
        tRPC queries served live
    end note
